public boolean isPalindrome(String str) {
    int left = 0;
    int right = str.length() - 1;
    while (left < right) {
        if (str.charAt(left) != str.charAt(right)) {
            return false;
        }
        left++;
        right--;
    }
    return true;
}

This function takes a string as input and uses two pointers to compare characters from the beginning and end of the string. If at any point the characters do not match, it returns false indicating that the string is not a palindrome. If the entire string is traversed without any mismatches, it returns true indicating that the string is a palindrome.

